<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1137153 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno-651x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1176" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno-651x598.jpg 651w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno-487x447.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno-974x895.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno-261x240.jpg 261w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno-523x480.jpg 523w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno-600x551.jpg 600w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/tekno.jpg 1054w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Tekno has just released a brand-new single titled “KATA”. The popular artiste has given his listeners a reason to smile this period as the song is about love and romantic promises. The song serves to remind people of the beautiful things of life like love, joy, friendship, bonds, and hope. With everything happening around the world and the unfortunate spread of Corona Virus, the multi-talented Nigerian singer, songwriter, and producer uses his music to uplift everyone, reminding us that we are not alone and together, we can overcome anything. The upbeat track is currently the No. 1 trending song on Triller, an entertainment and social video sharing platform, with over 850+ videos already created two days before its official release. With more national and international musicians hosting Live parties on social media during the COVID-19 period, Tekno will be releasing music more frequently during this period to help spread positive vibes as the world deals with the Corona Virus pandemic. Tekno, is a Nigerian musician, producer, performer, and dancer who signed a distribution deal with Universal Music Group Nigeria (UMGN), a division of Universal Music Group in charge of West Africa, as well as the UK-based Island Records in 2018. His popular songs include “skeleton”, “Samantha”, “Pana”, “Jogodo” and many more. Listen to the song below: https://umgafrica.lnk.to/Kata